<TITLE> Fatulla businessman stabbed to death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, July 13 (bdnews24.com)Alleged dacoits stabbed a businessman Shawkat Ali, 55 to death early Monday in South Qayyumpur of Fatulla Sadar. Three more persons were wounded during the robbery of whom critically injured Monir, 28 was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Konika, the daughter-in-law of the deceased said, at around 3 am, seven/eight masked men broke into the three-storey house by breaking open the collapsible gate of the ground floor. The intruders went up to the first floor, brought out weapons, intimidated the inmates and took them hostages by tying their hands and feet. They murdered the house master Shawkat Ali and looted 15 bhoris of gold and Tk 20, 000 in cash. The dacoits entered into a tenant Monir's room on the 1st floor and stabbed him too. The dead Shawkat Ali owned a tyre shop at Chasharha. Monir is a garments factory worker. 
